postcontent: The Smith & Wesson 5903 9mm pistol was introduced in 1990 as a lightweight alternative to the legendary all stainless 5906. The frame is high tech aluminum alloy which brings the weight down 1/2 lb. to just 26.5 ozs. unloaded while providing the same 5906 reliability so popular with law enforcement. Recoil is less than full size polymer frame pistols enabling enhanced follow up shot accuracy even though weight is only slightly higher. I'm a range shooter and simply have a "blast" consistantly nailing 2" target squares at 50 feet.   The stainless slide with a 4" barrel and Lo-Mount Novak 3 dot sights as well as the high capacity 15 round double stack magazines are interchangeable with the 5906.    The action is called Traditional Double Action (TDA) which describes a longer 1st shot trigger pull which cocks the hammer, and single action short crisp trigger pull on subsequent shots.    An ambidextrous safety / decocker is featured for convenience and ultimate safety especially when keeping a round chambered.   This pistol for sale has a 2/01/1994 manufacture date. It's been well cared for as you can see. There is little finish wear and few noticeable scratches. The internals are excellent and the recoil spring is new. This example was made by Weyersberg, Kirschbaum & Co. of Solingen, Germany.The three intertwined circles on the ricasso are the trademark of the famous steelworks, Krupp (pronounced 'Kroop'), who supplied the blade steel.
